Please follow the steps below to open the Certificate Manager and check whether the required Amazon root certificates are present on your system.
&nbsp;
How to Open Certificate Manager:
&nbsp;
Method 1 – Run Dialog
  Press Windows + R  Type: certmgr.msc  Press Enter  Method 2 – Command Prompt
  Type cmdcertmgr.msc  Press Enter  &nbsp;
What to Do Once Certificate Manager Opens:
&nbsp;
 Step 1: Navigate to Root Certificates   In the left pane, expand Trusted Root Certification Authorities  Click on the Certificates folder underneath it  You will see a list of all trusted root certificates installed on the system.   &nbsp;  Step 2: Search for Amazon Certificates Please check if any of the following certificates are present (the list is alphabetically sorted):
Amazon Root CA 1
Amazon Root CA 2
Amazon Root CA 3
Amazon Root CA 4
Starfield Services Root Certificate Authority – G2
&nbsp;
